  "dateModified": "2026-04-27",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "The condition of an autopoietic system whose operations refer only to its own states and produce only its own further operations — the system's environment perturbs but does not directly determine the operations, and meaning is generated within the system rather than received from outside.",
  "name": "Operational closure",
